---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import BrandBranchesGrid from '../../components/BrandBranchesGrid.astro';
import { MAIN_PHONE, MAIN_PHONE_TEL } from '../../data/branches';

const title = "JennAir Refrigerator Repair | Southern California | NOIR, RISE, Columns";
const description = "JennAir fridge repair across SoCal, NOIR, RISE, built-in columns, French Door (JF42/JFC), side-by-side (JS42). EPA 608 plus BHGS #A49573. $89 dx waived.";
const canonical = "https://samedayappliance.repair/brands/jennair-refrigerator-repair/";

const schemaJsons = [
  {
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "LocalBusiness",
    "@id": "https://samedayappliance.repair/brands/jennair-refrigerator-repair/#business",
    "name": "Same Day Appliance Repair, JennAir Refrigerator Service",
    "image": "https://samedayappliance.repair/images/same-day-appliance-repair.png",
    "url": "https://samedayappliance.repair/brands/jennair-refrigerator-repair/",
    "telephone": MAIN_PHONE_TEL,
    "priceRange": "$$$$"
  },
  {
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "Service",
    "serviceType": "JennAir Refrigerator Repair",
    "provider": { "@type": "LocalBusiness", "name": "Same Day Appliance Repair" },
    "areaServed": [
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Los Angeles County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Orange County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Ventura County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "San Bernardino County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Riverside County" }
    ],
    "offers": {
      "@type": "Offer",
      "priceSpecification": {
        "@type": "PriceSpecification",
        "price": "89.00",
        "priceCurrency": "USD",
        "description": "Diagnostic fee, waived with repair"
      }
    }
  },
  {
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "FAQPage",
    "mainEntity": [
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "My JennAir refrigerator won't cool, where do I start?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Systematic diagnostic. Step 1: check if compressor is running, put your hand on the back or side of the refrigerator; you should feel slight vibration and warm air from the condenser area. Silent refrigerator with warm cavity = compressor not starting, most common root cause is compressor start relay failure ($95-$155) OR inverter board failure on newer models like JS48 ($385-$485 genuine Embraco VCC2 board, OEM 12002799). Step 2: clean condenser coils, 80% of 'not cooling' calls resolve with condenser cleaning if coils haven't been cleaned in 12+ months ($95 flat service). Step 3: check evaporator fan behind freezer back panel, ice buildup or seized motor means no airflow between compartments ($245-$345). Step 4: defrost system, frost visible on evaporator coils means defrost heater, thermostat, or timer failed ($185-$345). Step 5: refrigerant leak (oily residue at compressor area), EPA 608 sealed-system service needed, $680-$1,280 depending on leak location."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "How do I put my JennAir refrigerator in diagnostic test mode?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Most current-generation JennAir refrigerators have a built-in diagnostic test mode. Procedure: within 2 seconds, press the internal light switch 3 times, then press and hold it a 4th time until you hear a long beep. You're now in test mode. Press the door switch twice within 2 seconds to start compressor test, control beeps twice, you should hear compressor start within a few seconds. Press door switch twice again to activate evaporator fan test. If either doesn't run during test, component failure is confirmed. Tech sheet with complete diagnostic procedure is usually located behind the bottom front grille or taped to the back of the refrigerator. This is the same Whirlpool Corporation diagnostic procedure used across JennAir, Kenmore, Maytag, and Whirlpool brands. We run diagnostic test mode on every cooling complaint service call, takes 2 minutes and rules in/out major components before ordering parts."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Is my JennAir the same platform as Whirlpool or KitchenAid?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Partially. JennAir refrigerators use Whirlpool Corporation's sealed-system components (compressors, condensers, evaporators) that are often shared with KitchenAid, Maytag, and Whirlpool equivalents, the same Embraco VCC2 inverter board that controls a JS48SEFXDSS compressor is used in select KitchenAid and Maytag models too. Core cooling engineering is cross-platform at Whirlpool Corp. What's JennAir-specific: the built-in installation architecture on columns and 42\"/48\" side-by-side built-ins (JS42, JS48, JF42), NOIR black finishes, RISE commercial handles, VitaFreshPlus humidity-controlled drawers, and some control board firmware. For service: cross-platform parts availability is a real advantage, common failures source parts in 1-2 days. JennAir-specific trim and panel items require genuine JennAir supply."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "My JS42 built-in side-by-side has ice maker issues",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "JS42 (42\" built-in side-by-side) ice maker issues are common service calls, most LA JennAir refrigerators we service are this model family. Five-step diagnostic. (1) Water supply line, verify not kinked, water valve fully open. (2) Water filter, clogged filter restricts flow, replace every 6 months per Bosch/JennAir spec ($45-$85 genuine JennAir filter). (3) Fill tube frozen, ice blockage prevents water entry, melt and clear with warm cloth (free). (4) Ice maker module failed, replacement $265-$365. (5) Water inlet valve solenoid failed, won't energize to fill ice maker, $185-$265 replacement. On 8+ year old JS42 units, we see ice maker module failures most often, component replacement typically at year 6-9."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "How much does JennAir refrigerator repair cost?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Diagnostic is $89, waived with repair. Typical JennAir refrigerator repairs: compressor start relay $95-$155, inverter board (Embraco VCC2, 12002799 for JS48 family) $385-$485, compressor replacement (out of warranty) $780-$1,380, evaporator fan motor $245-$345, condenser fan motor $225-$325, condenser coil cleaning $95 flat, defrost heater $225-$325, defrost thermostat $95-$145, defrost timer $145-$215, main control board $485-$685, thermistor (temperature sensor) $95-$145, ice maker module $265-$365, water inlet valve $185-$265, water filter replacement $45-$85, door gasket (column or side-by-side) $225-$385, NOIR door panel $385-$580 (JennAir-specific), door hinge (panel-ready columns) $185-$265, defrost drain tube clearing $85 flat, refrigerant leak repair (EPA 608) $680-$1,280. Labor and parts quoted before work starts."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Are JennAir columns a viable Sub-Zero alternative?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Yes, at a different price-and-aesthetic tier. Sub-Zero is the traditional luxury built-in refrigeration benchmark, 12-year sealed-system warranty, individually-tuned dual compressors, decades-long service life. JennAir columns (JF42 French-door, JS42/JS48 side-by-side built-in, panel-ready column options) offer similar built-in aesthetics and paneling at roughly 60-70% of Sub-Zero's price, with single-compressor architecture and shorter warranty (typically 1 year plus 5-year sealed system). Service reality: JennAir columns are serviceable throughout a 12-15 year life with component-level repairs, similar to Sub-Zero service logistics. The compressor and sealed system are Whirlpool Corporation engineering, robust but not the individually-tuned dual-compressor design of Sub-Zero. Good choice for contemporary kitchens where NOIR or RISE aesthetic fits the design vision better than Sub-Zero's traditional styling. See our <a href='/brands/sub-zero-refrigerator-repair/'>Sub-Zero refrigerator page</a> for the luxury built-in alternative."
        }
      }
    ]
  }
];
---
<Layout title={title} description={description} canonical={canonical}>
  <Fragment slot="head-scripts">
    {schemaJsons.map((schema) => (
      <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify(schema)} />
    ))}
  </Fragment>

  <section class="hero">
    <div class="hero-inner">
      <div class="hero-content">
        <p class="hero-eyebrow">LA · Orange · Ventura · San Bernardino · Riverside Counties</p>
        <h1>JennAir Refrigerator Repair</h1>
        <p class="hero-sub">Factory-trained service on JennAir (Jenn-Air) refrigerators, built-in columns, French-door (JF42, JFC), side-by-side (JS42, JS48, JCD), bottom-freezer (JBR), counter-depth. RISE and NOIR collections. Embraco VCC2 inverter board diagnostics (OEM 12002799). EPA 608 certified for sealed-system work. Post-warranty specialists for 3-to-15-year-old JennAir refrigerators.</p>
        <div class="hero-ctas">
          <a href={`tel:${MAIN_PHONE_TEL}`} class="btn-primary">☎ {MAIN_PHONE}</a>
          <a href="/contact/" class="btn-outline">Book Online</a>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="hero-img-wrap">
        <div class="hero-img-placeholder">
          <p>JennAir Refrigerator Repair</p>
          <p>Across Southern California</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <div class="trust-bar">
    <div class="trust-bar-inner">
      <div class="trust-item"><span class="trust-icon">🏅</span> BHGS Licensed #A49573</div>
      <div class="trust-item"><span class="trust-icon">❄</span> EPA 608 Certified</div>
      <div class="trust-item"><span class="trust-icon">⚡</span> Same Day Available</div>
      <div class="trust-item"><span class="trust-icon">🔩</span> OEM Parts on Truck</div>
      <div class="trust-item"><span class="trust-icon">💬</span> $89 Diagnostic, Waived With Repair</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ── INTRO ── -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container narrow">
      <p class="eyebrow-sub">About this service</p>
      <h2>JennAir refrigerators, design-forward luxury with Whirlpool Corp engineering backbone.</h2>
      <p>JennAir (also Jenn-Air, pronounced "Jen Air") refrigerators occupy a specific niche in the Southern California luxury refrigeration market. Built-in aesthetics and paneling that compete with Sub-Zero, at a tier below Sub-Zero's price and a tier above Samsung/LG mass-market. Modern design language, especially the NOIR Collection with matte black finishes, that fits contemporary and transitional LA kitchens better than Sub-Zero's traditional styling.</p>
      <p>The engineering reality: JennAir refrigerators use <strong>Whirlpool Corporation sealed-system components</strong>, compressors, condensers, evaporators, and control architecture often shared with KitchenAid, Maytag, and Whirlpool equivalents. The same <strong>Embraco VCC2 inverter board (OEM 12002799)</strong> that controls compressor speed on a JennAir JS48SEFXDSS is used in select KitchenAid and Maytag models. This cross-brand parts compatibility is a real advantage for service, excellent parts availability, competitive repair economics.</p>
      <p>What's JennAir-specific: the built-in installation architecture, NOIR matte-black trim and panels, RISE commercial handles, VitaFreshPlus humidity-controlled drawers, and control board firmware. These require genuine JennAir parts through standard distribution, typically same-week availability for common items.</p>
      <p>Most of our JennAir refrigerator calls are 4-to-12-year-old JS42 (42" built-in side-by-side), JF42 (French-door built-in), and JFC counter-depth units across Beverly Hills, Sherman Oaks, Brentwood, Studio City, Encino, Calabasas, and Pasadena on the LA side; Newport Coast, Newport Beach, and Tustin in OC; Westlake Village, Hidden Hills, and Thousand Oaks in Ventura; and Rancho Cucamonga and Temecula wine-country contemporary kitchens in the IE. Compressor start relay failures lead the list, followed by ice maker module issues on JS42 family, evaporator fan wear, and VitaFreshPlus sensor drift.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ── MODELS ── -->
  <section class="section section-alt">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="eyebrow-sub">Models we service</p>
      <h2>JennAir refrigerator model families</h2>

      <div class="model-grid">
        <div class="model-card">
          <h3>JS42 / JS48 Built-In Side-by-Side</h3>
          <p class="model-list">JS42PPDBDA · JS42CXDUDB02 · JS48SEFXDSS · JS48NXFXDE</p>
          <p>Flagship built-in side-by-side refrigerators. 42" and 48" widths. Panel-ready (owner's custom cabinet panels flush with surrounding cabinetry) or factory-finished RISE and NOIR options. Embraco VCC2 inverter board (OEM 12002799) on current generation. Most common JennAir refrigerator we service across our area, JS42 dominates 2015+ new construction and renovation across Sherman Oaks, Brentwood, Calabasas luxury homes plus Newport Coast and Westlake Village contemporary builds.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="model-card">
          <h3>JF42 French-Door Built-In Column</h3>
          <p class="model-list">JF42NXFXDE02 · JF42SSFXDA · JF42NXFXDB · JF42NXFXDE</p>
          <p>42" built-in French-door column. Two upper doors plus bottom drawer freezer configuration. Panel-ready on most variants. NOIR and RISE finish options. Common in Hollywood Hills modernist builds, LA Westside contemporary renovations, Newport Coast and Pelican Hill OC modernist kitchens, and Westlake Village and Hidden Hills design-forward estates where the owner wanted French-door accessibility with built-in cabinet integration. Shares core compressor and evaporator architecture with JS42 side-by-side.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="model-card">
          <h3>JFC French-Door Counter-Depth</h3>
          <p class="model-list">JFC2087HRS · JFC2089HES · JFC2089HTB · JFC2290REP00 · JFC2290VPF</p>
          <p>Counter-depth French-door refrigerators, flush with standard kitchen cabinetry depth without protruding, but not fully built-in like JF42 columns. 36" width typical. Common in mid-luxury renovations and newer builder-spec developments across our service area, Santa Monica, Mid-Wilshire, West Hollywood, Studio City on the LA side; Newport Beach, Tustin, and Irvine in OC; Westlake Village and Thousand Oaks in Ventura; and Rancho Cucamonga and Temecula contemporary builds. Lower price point than JF42 built-in columns, similar aesthetic result for cost-conscious luxury renovations.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="model-card">
          <h3>JCD / JSD Side-by-Side (Standard Depth)</h3>
          <p class="model-list">JCD2289AES · JCD2295KES · JCD2389GES · JSD2695KES · JSD2789GES</p>
          <p>Standard-depth side-by-side refrigerators, common in older JennAir installations 2000-2012. Still serviceable units; parts availability still good for common failures. Many homes across Westside LA, Pasadena, Newport Beach, Westlake Village, and the broader Southern California 1990s/2000s renovation cohort specified JCD, now reaching 15-20 year old service territory. Honest repair-vs-replace assessment for units in this age range.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="model-card">
          <h3>JBR Bottom-Freezer</h3>
          <p class="model-list">JBR2088HES · JBR2286TS · JBR2086HE</p>
          <p>Bottom-freezer refrigerators with freezer drawer below refrigerator compartment. Common in condos and smaller-footprint kitchens across our service area, Wilshire Corridor, Newport Beach high-rises, Long Beach towers, Marina del Rey waterfront, where space-efficient layout matters more than built-in aesthetics. Reliable workhorse design, fewer electronic complications than JS42/JS48 flagships, more conventional Whirlpool Corporation refrigeration architecture.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="model-card">
          <h3>RC5 Legacy Column / RDK Drawer</h3>
          <p class="model-list">RC5H/E7S02 · RC5HB/E8S00 · RDK226W · RDK246W</p>
          <p>Legacy JennAir columns (RC5 series, pre-2012) and under-counter drawer refrigerators (RDK). Still serviceable for common failures; some specialty components (NOIR-equivalent finishes, specialty controls) may have reduced parts availability on 15+ year units. Drawer refrigerators across Westside LA, Newport Beach, Westlake Village, and Temecula wine-country usually serve butler's pantries, bar setups, and dedicated beverage zones.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <p class="footnote">Model number prefix key: JS = built-in side-by-side (42", 48"). JF = built-in French-door column (42"). JFC = French-door counter-depth (36"). JCD/JSD = standard-depth side-by-side. JBR = bottom-freezer. RC5 = legacy column. RDK = drawer refrigerator.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ── DIAGNOSTIC TEST MODE ── -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container narrow">
      <p class="eyebrow-sub">Technical reference</p>
      <h2>JennAir diagnostic test mode, what we use during service</h2>
      <p>Most current-generation JennAir refrigerators (and their Whirlpool Corporation siblings) have a built-in diagnostic test mode that lets technicians verify component operation before ordering parts. Owners rarely access this, it's a service tool, but understanding that it exists explains why our factory-trained diagnostic is more efficient than general handyman troubleshooting.</p>
      <p><strong>Access procedure:</strong> within 2 seconds, press the internal refrigerator <strong>light switch 3 times</strong>, then press and hold the light switch a <strong>4th time</strong> until you hear a long beep. The refrigerator is now in test mode. Press the <strong>door switch twice</strong> within 2 seconds to start a compressor test, the control beeps twice and the compressor should start within a few seconds. Press door switch twice again to activate the evaporator fan test. If either component doesn't run during its test, the failure is confirmed at the component level rather than the control system.</p>
      <p>The tech sheet with complete diagnostic procedure is usually located behind the bottom front grille or taped to the back of the refrigerator. If the tech sheet is missing, we work from Whirlpool Corporation service manuals, this is the same diagnostic procedure used across JennAir, Kenmore, Maytag, and Whirlpool-branded units.</p>
      <p>What this means practically: when a technician visits and can't run diagnostic test mode, they're doing deductive troubleshooting rather than direct component verification. Same visit might take 90 minutes of testing vs 15 minutes in test mode. Factory-trained JennAir service consistently finishes diagnostics and part ordering within one visit.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ── COMMON PROBLEMS ── -->
  <section class="section section-alt">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="eyebrow-sub">Common failures</p>
      <h2>The ten things that break on a JennAir refrigerator</h2>

      <div class="problem">
        <h3>1. Compressor won't start, start relay or inverter board (#1 call)</h3>
        <p>Most common JennAir refrigerator call. Symptoms: silent refrigerator, cavity warming, no compressor vibration detectable. On older models (pre-2018), the culprit is usually compressor start relay, inexpensive component ($95-$155) that tells compressor to start. On current JS48 family (JS48SEFXDSS and relatives), it's the <strong>Embraco VCC2 inverter board</strong>, OEM 12002799, $385-$485 replacement. Diagnostic: run test mode (procedure above), compressor should start when commanded. If silent in test mode AND start relay tests OK, inverter board is the failure. This is the same Embraco part used in select Whirlpool and KitchenAid flagship refrigerators, so cross-brand availability is excellent.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="problem">
        <h3>2. Refrigerator warm, freezer cold, evaporator fan</h3>
        <p>Classic airflow imbalance. Evaporator fan behind freezer back panel circulates cold air between freezer and refrigerator compartments. When fan fails or ices over, freezer stays cold (where evaporator coil is) but refrigerator warms without air circulation. Diagnostic in test mode: fan should run audibly when commanded. Fan replacement $245-$345, 75-min job. Alternative cause: frost buildup on evaporator coils blocking airflow (see defrost failure below).</p>
      </div>

      <div class="problem">
        <h3>3. Condenser coils blocked, cooling efficiency loss</h3>
        <p>The fix everyone skips. Condenser coils at the back or bottom of refrigerator accumulate dust, pet hair, and (in LA coastal areas) salt residue over 12-24 months. Blocked coils make compressor work harder, refrigerator runs warmer, energy use spikes, compressor lifespan shortens. LA coastal: clean every 4-5 months. Inland: every 6 months. Professional cleaning $95 flat; DIY with coil brush and vacuum is free. For built-in JennAir columns (JF42, JS42), coils are at the top behind the grille, access often requires grille removal and specific toolkit.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="problem">
        <h3>4. Defrost system failure, frost on evaporator coils</h3>
        <p>JennAir refrigerators are frost-free; visible frost on freezer walls or evaporator coils means defrost cycle failed. Three components can fail. Defrost heater: melts frost during cycle, tests open or shorted ($225-$325). Defrost thermostat: tells heater to turn on/off at correct temperature ($95-$145). Defrost timer/sensor: triggers cycle every 8-12 hours ($145-$215). On 8+ year JS42 and JF42 units, thermostat is the most common single failure. Integrated defrost control on newer models means main control board replacement if discrete components test good, $485-$685.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="problem">
        <h3>5. Ice maker stopped working (JS42 family)</h3>
        <p>Most common secondary call on JS42 built-in side-by-sides. Five-step diagnostic. (1) Water supply line kinked or closed valve, free fix. (2) Water filter clogged, replace every 6 months, $45-$85 JennAir filter. (3) Fill tube frozen, melt with warm cloth, free fix. (4) Ice maker module failed, $265-$365 replacement, typical failure year 6-9. (5) Water inlet valve solenoid failed, $185-$265 replacement. On 10+ year JS42 units, we see ice maker module failures routinely, component is a maintenance item at this age.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="problem">
        <h3>6. VitaFreshPlus drawer produce not staying fresh</h3>
        <p>VitaFreshPlus is JennAir's humidity-controlled produce drawer system (similar to Bosch VitaFreshPro or Miele FreshZone). Independent humidity sensors maintain optimal humidity for different produce types. When produce quality drops, three causes. (1) Configuration mismatch, leafy greens in low-humidity drawer, fruits in high-humidity drawer; free diagnostic, common owner error. (2) Humidity sensor drift, $125-$185 sensor replacement. (3) Drawer seal damaged, humidity escapes, $85-$145 seal, free if just dirty/debris. We verify sensor calibration before ordering parts.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="problem">
        <h3>7. Water pooling at bottom of refrigerator</h3>
        <p>Defrost drain tube clogged. Melt-water from evaporator routes through tube to drain pan under compressor; when tube clogs, water backs up into refrigerator. Fix: pull refrigerator from wall, access back panel near compressor, clear tube with brush and warm soapy water. $85 flat on our side, or DIY if comfortable with refrigerator pull-out. Prevention: wipe spills promptly, avoid leaving food debris that could enter drain pathway. On built-in JennAir columns (JF42, JS42), drain tube access is from top, different procedure but same underlying repair.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="problem">
        <h3>8. Unusual noises, diagnostic by sound</h3>
        <p>Different sounds indicate different components. Loud humming at start = compressor struggling, early-stage start relay or inverter board. Rattling/clicking = fan blade hitting ice buildup (defrost lagged), free fix with defrost cycle and inspection. High-pitched whine = fan motor bearing wear, $245-$345 replacement. Gurgling/hissing = normal refrigerant movement, not a repair. Clicking from compressor area = start relay trying to engage and failing, $95-$155 replacement. Rhythmic thumping = condenser fan blade damaged or loose, $145-$225.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="problem">
        <h3>9. Thermistor failure, inaccurate temperatures</h3>
        <p>Thermistor (temperature sensor) monitors refrigerator and freezer cavity temperatures, reports to control board for cycling decisions. When thermistor drifts, refrigerator may run too cold (freezing lettuce), too warm (spoilage), or cycle erratically. Diagnostic: control board shows measured temperature vs setpoint, drift indicates sensor. Replacement $95-$145 per sensor, 45-min job. On JS42/JS48, there are typically 3 thermistors (refrigerator cavity, freezer cavity, evaporator), we identify which has drifted before ordering.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="problem">
        <h3>10. Refrigerant leak, oily residue at compressor</h3>
        <p>Rare but occurs on 10+ year units. Signatures: oily residue around compressor housing, refrigerator not cooling despite compressor running, audible hissing. Requires <strong>EPA 608 certified sealed-system service</strong>, all our technicians are certified. Leak location determines cost: evaporator leak (most common) $680-$980; condenser or compressor leak $880-$1,180; line-set leak $780-$1,080. We identify exact leak location, repair or replace affected component, evacuate system, recharge with correct refrigerant quantity (R-134A on most JennAir units). Sealed-system work not DIY under federal law, requires certification and specialized equipment.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ── COMPARISON SECTION ── -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container narrow">
      <p class="eyebrow-sub">Positioning</p>
      <h2>JennAir columns vs Sub-Zero, honest comparison</h2>
      <p>If you're considering service, you've already chosen JennAir, this section is for the service context, not a sales pitch. But understanding the positioning helps explain service economics.</p>
      <p><strong>Sub-Zero</strong> is the traditional luxury built-in refrigeration benchmark. 12-year sealed-system warranty (industry-leading), individually-tuned dual compressors, decades-long service life. Homes across our service area with Sub-Zero often serve that refrigerator for 20-25 years with component-level repairs. Service economics favor repair strongly, we process 12-year sealed-system warranty claims regularly.</p>
      <p><strong>JennAir columns</strong> (JF42 French-door built-in, JS42/JS48 built-in side-by-side, panel-ready options) offer similar built-in aesthetics and paneling at roughly 60-70% of Sub-Zero's price. Single-compressor architecture, shorter base warranty (typically 1 year + 5-year sealed system on some models). 12-15 year service life is realistic with component-level repairs. Compressor and sealed system are Whirlpool Corporation engineering, robust, but not individually-tuned dual-compressor design.</p>
      <p>For service: JennAir columns are serviceable throughout their design life. Parts availability is strong due to Whirlpool Corp cross-brand compatibility. Compressor replacement at year 10-13 is the major cost event that separates long-term Sub-Zero economics from JennAir, Sub-Zero units this age still have years of warranty coverage; JennAir units are fully out-of-warranty and compressor replacement runs $780-$1,380.</p>
      <p>The strategic choice when both were specified: Sub-Zero for owners prioritizing decades-long service life and willing to pay premium for it. JennAir for owners prioritizing design aesthetic (especially NOIR) and willing to trade some longevity for contemporary styling at lower initial cost.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ── PRICING ── -->
  <section class="section section-alt">
    <div class="container narrow">
      <p class="eyebrow-sub">Pricing</p>
      <h2>What JennAir refrigerator repair usually costs</h2>
      <p>Diagnostic $89, waived with repair. Labor and parts quoted separately before work starts.</p>
      <table class="price-table">
        <thead>
          <tr><th>Repair</th><th>Typical range</th></tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td>Compressor start relay</td><td>$95 – $155</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Embraco VCC2 inverter board (OEM 12002799)</td><td>$385 – $485</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Compressor replacement (out of warranty)</td><td>$780 – $1,380</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Evaporator fan motor</td><td>$245 – $345</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Condenser fan motor</td><td>$225 – $325</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Condenser coil cleaning (preventive)</td><td>$95 flat</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Defrost heater</td><td>$225 – $325</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Defrost thermostat</td><td>$95 – $145</td></tr>
